        public TestResult​(UnitTest unitTest,
                  java.nio.file.Path submission,
                  java.nio.file.Path output,
                  TestState state)
           throws java.io.IOException
        Create a TestResult instance for a unit test
        Parameters:
        unitTest - The unit test the instance is instantiated from
        submission - The submission used in the unit test, as an absolute path
        output - The compiler or runtime output, depending on state
        state - The test state
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If an I/O error occurs while reading the output
        API Note:
        If an error occured during the compilation phase, use TestResult(UnitTest, Path, CompilationException)
